"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"FAUNA:2.28\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">2.28</span> 標題：騾子（mule）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來：פֶּרֶד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯：pered)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:29\">2SA 13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:9\">2SA 18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:9\">2SA 18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:9\">2SA 18:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:25\">1KI 10:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:5\">1KI 18:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:17\">2KI 5:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:41\">1CH 12:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:24\">2CH 9:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:66\">EZR 2:66</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:9\">PSA 32:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:20\">ISA 66:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:14\">EZK 27:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:15\">ZEC 14:15</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來：פִּרְדָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯：pirdah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:33\">1KI 1:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:38\">1KI 1:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:44\">1KI 1:44</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希：ἡμίονος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯：hēmionos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob2:17\">JDT 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Tob15:11\">JDT 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc5:43\">1ES 5:43</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">討論</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>希伯來文<em>pirdah</em> 指的是母騾，而<em>pered</em> 既可以指公騾，也可以指母騾。在聖經時期，騾子供人騎乘和用作馱畜，而馬主要用來拉戰車。騾子引入迦南的時間似乎比馬晚得多。約瑟的故事提到了馬，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:16\">DEU 17:16</a> 禁止王加添馬匹，然而直到大衛時期，聖經才提到騾子。嚴格來說，聖經並沒有明文禁止飼養騾子，但<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:19\">LEV 19:19</a> 禁止動物雜交，因此繁殖騾子也屬於被禁範圍。這樣，以色列人的騾子似乎依賴於從鄰國進口。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p><figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/PTZ-0098_mule_turning_olive_press.jpg\" alt=\"PTZ-0098_mule_turning_olive_press\"></figure>騾子並不是一種天然就有的動物，牠是人們用公驢和母馬雜交繁殖的結果。也可以用公馬和母驢來繁殖，但從動物學上來說，牠們的後代是「駃騠」，而不是「騾子」，通常比騾子小。騾子的體型和力氣都比驢大，也比馬和驢更能抵抗疾病。騾子通常是深褐色，耳朵比母馬大。</p>\n<p>雖然騾子也分公母，但是牠們不能生育，不能繁殖後代。因此，強壯的公騾比公馬更容易駕馭。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">特殊意義或象徵意義</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>在英文中，騾子與固執聯繫在一起，但在其他文化中卻通常並非如此，因為如果處理得當，騾子很容易駕馭。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:9\">PSA 32:9</a> 將騾子和馬一併講論，因為兩者都缺乏悟性，需要有人把牠們引導到正確的方向。</p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>即使在知道騾子的社會中，人們也常把牠們稱為「馬驢」或「驢馬」。因此，如果目標語言沒有表示騾子的詞語，那麼這是一個很好的譯法。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
